HB 849/24 – APP
By: Delegates Acevero, Addison, Alston, Bhandari, Chang, Fennell, Foley, Forbes,
Griffith, Harrison, Hinebaugh, Hornberger, Ivey, S. Johnson, D. Jones,
Kaiser, Martinez, Metzgar, Mireku–North, Roberson, Ruff, Shetty, Smith,
Spiegel, Terrasa, Turner, Williams, Wilson, Woods, and Woorman
Introduced and read first time: January 30, 2026
Assigned to: Appropriations
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 4, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Human Services – Universal Basic Income for Transition–Age Youth Foster Care
3 Transition Grant Program – Establishment
4 FOR the purpose of establishing the Universal Basic Income for Transition–Age Youth
5 Foster Care Transition Grant Program in the Department of Human Services;
6 providing that payments made under the Program may not be considered income or
7 resources for purposes of determining eligibility for certain benefits; requiring the
8 Department to report annually on the Program to the General Assembly; and
9 generally relating to the Universal Basic Income for Transition–Age Youth Foster
10 Care Transition Grant Program.
11 BY adding to
12 Article – Human Services
13 Section 5–5C–01 through 5–5C–04 to be under the new subtitle “Subtitle 5C.
14 Universal Basic Income for Transition–Age Youth Foster Care Transition
15 Grant Program”
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
19 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0628*

2 HOUSE BILL 628
1 Article – Human Services
2 SUBTITLE 5C. UNIVERSAL BASIC INCOME FOR TRANSITION–AGE YOUTH FOSTER
3 CARE TRANSITION GRANT PROGRAM.
4 5–5C–01.
5 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE, THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
6 INDICATED.
7 (B) “PROGRAM” MEANS THE UNIVERSAL BASIC INCOME FOR
8 TRANSITION–AGE YOUTH FOSTER CARE TRANSITION GRANT PROGRAM.
9 (C) “UNIVERSAL BASIC INCOME” MEANS UNCONDITIONAL CASH PAYMENTS
10 OF EQUAL AMOUNTS DISTRIBUTED MONTHLY TO ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS.
11 5–5C–02.
12 (A) THERE IS A UNIVERSAL BASIC INCOME FOR TRANSITION–AGE YOUTH
13 FOSTER CARE TRANSITION GRANT PROGRAM WITHIN THE DEPARTMENT.
14 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO PROVIDE FOR THE ECONOMIC
15 SECURITY OF INDIVIDUALS AGING OUT OF THE OUT–OF–HOME PLACEMENT
16 PROGRAM.
17 5–5C–03.
18 (A) AN BEGINNING IN FISCAL YEAR 2028, AN INDIVIDUAL SHALL BE
19 ELIGIBLE FOR A UNIVERSAL BASIC INCOME FOSTER CARE TRANSITION GRANT OF
20 $1,000 PER MONTH FOR A PERIOD OF 3 YEARS 1 YEAR IF:
21 (1) THE INDIVIDUAL RESIDED IN AN OUT–OF–HOME PLACEMENT ON
22 THE INDIVIDUAL’S 18TH BIRTHDAY, REGARDLESS OF THE AGE AT WHICH THE
23 INDIVIDUAL ENTERED OUT–OF–HOME PLACEMENT; AND
24 (2) THE INDIVIDUAL’S 18TH BIRTHDAY IS ON OR AFTER OCTOBER 1,
25 2026.
26 (B) PAYMENTS GRANTS ISSUED UNDER THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE
27 CONSIDERED INCOME OR RESOURCES FOR PURPOSES OF DETERMINING
28 ELIGIBILITY TO RECEIVE BENEFITS OR THE AMOUNTS OF BENEFITS RECEIVED FOR
29 THE FOLLOWING, AS PERMITTED BY FEDERAL LAW:

HOUSE BILL 628 3
1 (1) THE MARYLAND MEDICAL ASSISTANCE PROGRAM;
2 (2) THE MARYLAND EARNED INCOME TAX CREDIT; OR
3 (3) STATE AND FEDERAL FINANCIAL AID AND COLLEGE SUPPORT
4 PROGRAMS.
5 5–5C–04.
6 ON OR BEFORE OCTOBER 1, 2027 2028, AND EACH OCTOBER 1 THEREAFTER,
7 THE DEPARTMENT SHALL SUBMIT A REPORT TO THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY, IN
8 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, THAT
9 CONTAINS DESCRIPTIVE INFORMATION AND OUTCOME MEASURES OF PROGRAM
10 RECIPIENTS DURING THE PREVIOUS YEAR, INCLUDING, AT A MINIMUM:
11 (1) THE STARTING INCOME OF EACH RECIPIENT, EXCLUSIVE OF
12 UNIVERSAL BASIC INCOME PAYMENTS A FOSTER CARE TRANSITION GRANT;
13 (2) GEOGRAPHIC INFORMATION ABOUT EACH RECIPIENT, INCLUDING
14 COUNTY, CITY, AND ZIP CODE OF RESIDENCE;
15 (3) THE EMPLOYMENT STATUS OF EACH RECIPIENT BEFORE
16 RECEIVING UNIVERSAL BASIC INCOME PAYMENTS A FOSTER CARE TRANSITION
17 GRANT; AND
18 (4) THE HOUSING STATUS OF EACH RECIPIENT BEFORE RECEIVING
19 UNIVERSAL BASIC INCOME PAYMENTS A FOSTER CARE TRANSITION GRANT.
20 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
21 October 1, 2026. It shall remain effective for a period of 5 years and, at the end of September
22 30, 2031, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly, shall be
23 abrogated and of no further force and effect.
Approved:
